{
  "text": "Where: cost = cost of the heat exchanger q = thermal duty \u2206T m = mean temperature. Table 6 shows a selection of the cost data represented by the values of C UA [CITATION_1] . This table is prepared for an application between gas as a hot fluid at a medium pressure of about 2 MPa and cold fluid as treated water. An extensive set of C UA data for various heat exchangers can be found in ESDU (1994). Table 6 . Cost data CUA vs. UA for various heat exchanger types [CITATION_2] , ESDU (1994))",
